canonical:
  title: 賀表
  author: 李穀
  language: lzh
  text: 三陽協序肇頒象魏之和萬國朝元益衍慈闈之慶光增日月喜溢寰區云云道配乾剛德侔坤順怡神淵懿得女中堯舜之名佑聖憂勤措天下羲軒之世式迓佳辰之復茂膺諸福之臻云云端遇昌期獲叨洪造阻參賀列邈居東土之封第貢忠誠願上南山之壽
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀表
  author: 李穀
  language: lzh
  text: 三陽協序。肇頒象魏之和。萬國朝元。益衍慈闈之慶。光增日月。喜溢寰區。云云。道配乾剛。德侔坤順。怡神淵懿。得女中堯舜之名。佑聖憂勤。措天下羲軒之世。式迓佳辰之復。茂膺諸福之臻。云云。端遇昌期。獲叨洪造。阻參賀列。邈居東土之封。第貢忠誠。願上南山之壽。
korean:
  title: 하표
  author: 이곡
  language: kor
  text: 삼양(三陽)이 협동하는 철에 비로소 위궐(魏闕)의 화기(和氣)를 반포하고, 만국(萬國)이 신정(新正)에 조회하여 더욱 자위(慈闈)의 경사를 더하오니, 빛이 해와 달에 더하고 기쁨이 온 누리에 넘치옵나이다. 운운. 도(道)는 건강(乾剛)을 짝하시고, 덕(德)은 곤순(坤順)을 체(體)하시어 심신(心神)을 연의(淵懿)하게 즐기사 여중요순(女中堯舜)의 이름을 얻으시고, 성인(聖人)의 우근(憂勤)을 도우시어 천하를 희헌(羲軒) 세상으로 만드셨사오니, 이제 가신(佳辰)이 돌아옴을 맞아 그지없는 복을 받으리로소이다. 운운. 마침 성대(盛代)를 만나 외람되이 성은(聖恩)을 더럽혀 왔사오나, 멀리 동토(東土)의 봉강(封彊)에 살아 하열(賀列)에 참가치 못하옵고, 남산(南山)의 수(壽)를 올려 다만 충성을 드리옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0170&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 희헌(羲軒) : '
    value: 복희씨(伏羲氏)와 황제(黃帝)  헌원씨(軒轅氏) 시대의 성세(聖世).
english:
  title: A Congratulatory Memorial
  author: Lee Gok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    When the three months of spring align in harmonious accord, the imperial palace first radiates its benevolent atmosphere to all. As ten thousand nations gather in reverence at the new beginning, the blessings of the inner court multiply and flourish. Light grows brighter than sun and moon; joy overflows to every corner of the realm.

    The Way mirrors the strength of Heaven; Virtue embodies the compliance of Earth. With serene and lofty spirit, she has earned the name of a sage among women—a Yao or Shun of her sex. Supporting the sacred burden of care and diligence, she transforms the world into an age of the ancients, as in the time of Fuxi and the Yellow Emperor. Now as this auspicious season returns once more, boundless blessings shall surely come to pass.

    Fortunate am I to encounter this glorious age, undeserving as I am of such grace. Yet dwelling far in the eastern lands beyond the borders, I cannot join the assembly of well-wishers. Still, I offer the blessings of Nanshan's longevity and pledge my humble loyalty.
  footnotes:
    - The 'three months of spring' refers to the beginning of the year and the spring season, symbolizing renewal and the start of auspicious times.
    - The 'inner court' (慈闈) refers to the empress or the royal women's quarters.
    - Yao and Shun were legendary sage-kings of ancient China, representing the height of virtuous rulership.
    - Fuxi and the Yellow Emperor (Xuanyuan) represent the golden age of ancient Chinese civilization.
    - Nanshan refers to longevity and blessings, as in the expression 'may your years be as numerous as the southern mountains.'
